						<summary>

						<p>On the four faces of a pillar lying beside the house of Alauddin Phakir.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tailapa II 10th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The top portion of the pillar is broken and lost. It seems to record a gift made to a certain Chandrarāsi by the king Tailaparasa and his ministers.</p>						

						<p>There is a reference at the beginning of the record to a Śivabhakta Nārāyaṇa and his lineage. Also there is a reference to a <hi rend="italic">dīkshāguru</hi> whose particulars are not clear.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of about the 10th century A.D. </p>						

						</summary>
